window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>“Jason Kasper’s American Mercenary series boils with bold action, exotic locales, and spell-binding intrigue.” (Mark Greaney, number one <i>New York Times</i> best-selling Author of the Gray Man series)</p> <p>Before he was an assassin, David Rivers was a patriot.</p> <p>One year after the 9/11 attacks, he serves as an Army Ranger in Afghanistan.</p> <p>His patrol enters the Shigal Valley, a desolate place with a fearsome reputation for enemy fighters - a reputation that David is about to experience firsthand.</p> <p>As the first shots ring out over the valley, David must decide between military orders and gut instinct...and in the process, discover a hidden truth about himself.</p> <p>Perfect for fans of Vince Flynn, Brad Thor, Mark Greaney, and Brad Taylor. </p>"; 
